encoding iteration 2:

Overview:
[Opcode]

Opcode:
[opcode size][opcode enum number]

bits 0-5 = opcode enum
bits 6-7 = opcode size

opcode enum:
00 = 1 byte
01 = 2 bytes
10 = 3 bytes
11 = 4 bytes

NOTE: 
USE LEB128 for encoding immediates,
it removes I64 I8 I16 and replaces it
with a single IMM encoding

00 = (1*8)-2 bits (6 bits)
01 = (2*8)-2 bits (14 bits)
10 = (3*8)-2 bits (22 bits)
11 = (4*8)-2 bits (30 bits)

Assume ADD_R64_R64 operations are 0000 0110
Assume R0 is 0000 0000
Assume R15 is 0000 1111

ADD_R64_R64 R0, R15
THEREFORE EQUALS:

[0000 0110] + [0000 0000] + [0000 1111]

0x06 0x00 0x0F

ADD_R64_R64_S R0, R15
Equals:

[0000 0111] + [0000 1111]

0x07 0x0F

